15/09/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Greek Foreign Minister Dora Bakoyannis' was in Belgrade Thursday (14 September) for talks with President Boris Tadic and Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica.
She told them that only a compromise on Kosovo would secure stability in the region.
Tadic reiterated that an independent Kosovo was unacceptable for Serbia.
Bakoyannis next travelled to Pristina, where she met Kosovo government and political party leaders, as well as UNMIK chief Joachim Ruecker.
In other news, during a visit to Peja on Thursday, UN Principal Deputy Special Representative Steven Schook condemned violence in the province, citing an explosion Monday night that destroyed a house belonging to a Serb returnee in the village of Shtuple.
No one was injured in the incident.
The house was constructed, with financing from the UNDP, as part of a campaign to help Serbs return to Kosovo.
The UNDP has reportedly pledged to rebuild it.
(Naftemporiki, Kathimerini, Danas, Albanian News, ANA-MPA, Tanjug, Makfax, UPI, AP - 15/09/06;
AP, UN News Centre - 14/09/06;
Kosovo.net - 12/09/06)
